    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen working on #26334 I discovered then starting Neovim with `-E` flag doesn't result into full redraw. In particular, it doesn't update statusline color if there is `--cmd` option with `colorscheme` command. Not sure if this works as intended or even important, but decided to create an issue to keep track.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `nvim_new --clean -E --cmd 'colorscheme blue'`. This results into applied `blue` color scheme but with a different statusline color. Typing `redraw` command makes everything up to date (including statusline). \n\n### Expected behavior\n\nColor scheme is fully in effect as a result of `--cmd 'colorscheme blue'`.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-1741+gc45d1e32a\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNot sure, as it doesn't show statusline even with `set laststatus=2`\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS Linux x86_64 (6.6.2-arch1-1)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst-0.9\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nst-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
